{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/recipes/world-cup-2014-8-course-meal","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Confession - I'm not the biggest World Cup aficionado.  In fact, I started reading sport's magazines right before the event so that I could \"sound like\" I knew what I was talking about should I accidentally end up in conversation about football.</p>\n<p>But I never miss an opportunity to explore world cuisines, and I thought the World Cup's round of 16 would be the perfect time to tackle the foods of all 16 nations (a bit ridiculous, I know,  especially because I started planning yesterday and certainly wouldn't have enough time to do these dishes justice, even if I had enough time...but alas, here I go)</p>\n<p>This will be a classic 8-Course dinner with all the trimmings.  I'll be blending the cuisine of one team with that of the other, so for example, for Brazil and Chile, I made a \"Brasilia Sour\" - a play on the Brunswick sour, which has rum, lime, sugar - (a daiquiri) and merlot.  For the Brasilia Sour, I used Cachaca, gum syrup, lime juice, and floated a Chilean Malbec on top of it.  Let me tell you, it was yummy!  You have the sourness from the daiquiri side, but the Cachaca was mellowed out by the sugar and lime.  At the same time, you always get a little bit of a cinnamon-y flavor from the Malbec.</p>\n<p>The trick to the drink though was floating the Malbec on top.  You can pour the Malbec slowly over the back of a spoon to achieve this.  If you can get a spout to pour the Malbec out of, it is even better.</p>\n<p><strong>Ingredients</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>1.5 oz Cachaca</li>\n<li>3.25 oz lime juice</li>\n<li>.5 oz gum syrup</li>\n<li>1.5 oz Chilean Malbec</li>\n<li>strip of lime zest (garnish)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>DIRECTIONS</strong></p>\n<h4 id=\"1-in-a-shaker-put-in-cachaca-lime-juice-and-gum-syrup-over-some-ice-cubes--shake-until-combined-pour-in-coup-glass\"><a href=\"#1-in-a-shaker-put-in-cachaca-lime-juice-and-gum-syrup-over-some-ice-cubes--shake-until-combined-pour-in-coup-glass\" aria-label=\"1 in a shaker put in cachaca lime juice and gum syrup over some ice cubes  shake until combined pour in coup glass permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. In a shaker, put in Cachaca, lime juice, and gum syrup over some ice cubes.  Shake until combined. Pour in coup glass.</h4>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/257680698c983fedfd3a2247681f8e8e/3ed1b/84-2.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"84 2\" title=\"84 2\" src=\"/static/257680698c983fedfd3a2247681f8e8e/3d0fe/84-2.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/257680698c983fedfd3a2247681f8e8e/90185/84-2.jpg 450w,\n/static/257680698c983fedfd3a2247681f8e8e/7288a/84-2.jpg 900w,\n/static/257680698c983fedfd3a2247681f8e8e/3d0fe/84-2.jpg 1800w,\n/static/257680698c983fedfd3a2247681f8e8e/3ebb7/84-2.jpg 2700w,\n/static/257680698c983fedfd3a2247681f8e8e/15e1d/84-2.jpg 3600w,\n/static/257680698c983fedfd3a2247681f8e8e/3ed1b/84-2.jpg 5184w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/beaae33506fba743c4914940699755cd/3ed1b/84-3.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"84 3\" title=\"84 3\" src=\"/static/beaae33506fba743c4914940699755cd/3d0fe/84-3.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/beaae33506fba743c4914940699755cd/90185/84-3.jpg 450w,\n/static/beaae33506fba743c4914940699755cd/7288a/84-3.jpg 900w,\n/static/beaae33506fba743c4914940699755cd/3d0fe/84-3.jpg 1800w,\n/static/beaae33506fba743c4914940699755cd/3ebb7/84-3.jpg 2700w,\n/static/beaae33506fba743c4914940699755cd/15e1d/84-3.jpg 3600w,\n/static/beaae33506fba743c4914940699755cd/3ed1b/84-3.jpg 5184w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<h4 id=\"2-using-the-back-of-a-spoon-slowly-pour-malbec-and-float-on-top-of-the-cachaca-lime-juice-and-syrup\"><a href=\"#2-using-the-back-of-a-spoon-slowly-pour-malbec-and-float-on-top-of-the-cachaca-lime-juice-and-syrup\" aria-label=\"2 using the back of a spoon slowly pour malbec and float on top of the cachaca lime juice and syrup permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. Using the back of a spoon, slowly pour Malbec and float on top of the Cachaca, lime juice, and syrup.</h4>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/e09e34fdfbac73720a08fdaaac285bd9/3ed1b/84-4.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"84 4\" title=\"84 4\" src=\"/static/e09e34fdfbac73720a08fdaaac285bd9/3d0fe/84-4.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/e09e34fdfbac73720a08fdaaac285bd9/90185/84-4.jpg 450w,\n/static/e09e34fdfbac73720a08fdaaac285bd9/7288a/84-4.jpg 900w,\n/static/e09e34fdfbac73720a08fdaaac285bd9/3d0fe/84-4.jpg 1800w,\n/static/e09e34fdfbac73720a08fdaaac285bd9/3ebb7/84-4.jpg 2700w,\n/static/e09e34fdfbac73720a08fdaaac285bd9/15e1d/84-4.jpg 3600w,\n/static/e09e34fdfbac73720a08fdaaac285bd9/3ed1b/84-4.jpg 5184w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<h4 id=\"3-with-a-zester-zest-a-strip-of-lime-peel--use-as-garnish\"><a href=\"#3-with-a-zester-zest-a-strip-of-lime-peel--use-as-garnish\" aria-label=\"3 with a zester zest a strip of lime peel  use as garnish permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>3. With a zester, zest a strip of lime peel.  Use as garnish.</h4>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 1800px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/f3b7fedd79fa49dd9966e15a5bc8e38d/3ed1b/84-1.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"84 1\" title=\"84 1\" src=\"/static/f3b7fedd79fa49dd9966e15a5bc8e38d/3d0fe/84-1.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/f3b7fedd79fa49dd9966e15a5bc8e38d/90185/84-1.jpg 450w,\n/static/f3b7fedd79fa49dd9966e15a5bc8e38d/7288a/84-1.jpg 900w,\n/static/f3b7fedd79fa49dd9966e15a5bc8e38d/3d0fe/84-1.jpg 1800w,\n/static/f3b7fedd79fa49dd9966e15a5bc8e38d/3ebb7/84-1.jpg 2700w,\n/static/f3b7fedd79fa49dd9966e15a5bc8e38d/15e1d/84-1.jpg 3600w,\n/static/f3b7fedd79fa49dd9966e15a5bc8e38d/3ed1b/84-1.jpg 5184w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1800px) 100vw, 1800px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p>My second course is a Colombia and Uruguay appetizer slider - if you will.  I combined Colombia's arepas, which are these cornmeal style cakes with Uruguay's choripan, which is like a chorizo sandwich with chimichurri sauce.  I honestly did not think the arepas would turn out that good because of how simple the recipe was, but man did it!  The arepa choripan tasted like this really delicious and slightly spicy sandwich enveloped by these corn chip - like bread buns.  The flavors really blew me away, and although I'm sure I didn't do the foods its due justice, I know I'll be trying Colombian and Uruguayan cuisine again.</p>\n<p>A note is that the cooked corn flour used in the arepas, masarepa, can actually be found in the international or Latin section of most grocery stores.</p>\n<p>For Arepas:</p>\n<p>** Ingredients**</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 1/2 cups masarepa </li>\n<li>1 1/2 cups water</li>\n<li>1 teaspoon vegetable oil</li>\n<li>Kosher salt</li>\n<li>3 teaspoons butter (1 teaspoon reserved for frying)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"1-combine-masarepa-water-vegetable-oil-salt-and-butter-into-a-bowl-knead-for-2-3-minutes-until-dough-ball-is-formed\"><a href=\"#1-combine-masarepa-water-vegetable-oil-salt-and-butter-into-a-bowl-knead-for-2-3-minutes-until-dough-ball-is-formed\" aria-label=\"1 combine masarepa water vegetable oil salt and butter into a bowl knead for 2 3 minutes until dough ball is formed permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. Combine masarepa, water, vegetable oil, salt, and butter into a bowl. Knead for 2-3 minutes until dough ball is formed.</h4>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 726px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/03f918f64ab7fe82264daa43514b0ffd/4e1b0/83-2.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"83 2\" title=\"83 2\" src=\"/static/03f918f64ab7fe82264daa43514b0ffd/4e1b0/83-2.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/03f918f64ab7fe82264daa43514b0ffd/90185/83-2.jpg 450w,\n/static/03f918f64ab7fe82264daa43514b0ffd/4e1b0/83-2.jpg 726w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/7edee557bc19daddf2ff9c29b58e6e9d/f9294/83-3.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"83 3\" title=\"83 3\" src=\"/static/7edee557bc19daddf2ff9c29b58e6e9d/f9294/83-3.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/7edee557bc19daddf2ff9c29b58e6e9d/90185/83-3.jpg 450w,\n/static/7edee557bc19daddf2ff9c29b58e6e9d/f9294/83-3.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<h4 id=\"2-divide-dough-into-10-even-pieces-and-roll-into-ball--between-2-sheets-of-plastic-wrap-roll-dough-out-into-14-inch-thick-disks\"><a href=\"#2-divide-dough-into-10-even-pieces-and-roll-into-ball--between-2-sheets-of-plastic-wrap-roll-dough-out-into-14-inch-thick-disks\" aria-label=\"2 divide dough into 10 even pieces and roll into ball  between 2 sheets of plastic wrap roll dough out into 14 inch thick disks permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>2. Divide dough into 10 even pieces and roll into ball.  Between 2 sheets of plastic wrap, roll dough out into 1/4 inch thick disks.</h4>\n<p>!<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 726px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/51c014034ce2c7f52a744be399fcec19/4e1b0/83-4.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"83 4\" title=\"83 4\" src=\"/static/51c014034ce2c7f52a744be399fcec19/4e1b0/83-4.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/51c014034ce2c7f52a744be399fcec19/90185/83-4.jpg 450w,\n/static/51c014034ce2c7f52a744be399fcec19/4e1b0/83-4.jpg 726w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure></p>\n<h4 id=\"3-in-a-non-stick-pan-over-medium-to-medium-high-heat-melt-a-pad-of-butter-with-several-tablespoons-of-vegetable-oil--put-in-arepas-and-fry-for-3-4-minutes-each-side-until-golden-and-slightly-charred--remove-and-drain-on-paper-towel--place-on-cooling-rack\"><a href=\"#3-in-a-non-stick-pan-over-medium-to-medium-high-heat-melt-a-pad-of-butter-with-several-tablespoons-of-vegetable-oil--put-in-arepas-and-fry-for-3-4-minutes-each-side-until-golden-and-slightly-charred--remove-and-drain-on-paper-towel--place-on-cooling-rack\" aria-label=\"3 in a non stick pan over medium to medium high heat melt a pad of butter with several tablespoons of vegetable oil  put in arepas and fry for 3 4 minutes each side until golden and slightly charred  remove and drain on paper towel  place on cooling rack permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>3. In a non-stick pan over medium to medium-high heat, melt a pad of butter with several tablespoons of vegetable oil.  Put in arepas and fry for 3-4 minutes each side until golden and slightly charred.  Remove and drain on paper towel.  Place on cooling rack.</h4>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 674px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/b66162d44c4d567492c75714fad51873/f9294/83-6.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.61721068249258%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"83 6\" title=\"83 6\" src=\"/static/b66162d44c4d567492c75714fad51873/f9294/83-6.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/b66162d44c4d567492c75714fad51873/90185/83-6.jpg 450w,\n/static/b66162d44c4d567492c75714fad51873/f9294/83-6.jpg 674w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p>For Chimichurri Sauce:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 Bunch parsley </li>\n<li>1/2 cup oregano</li>\n<li>10 cloves garlic </li>\n<li>2 seeded hot red peppers</li>\n<li>1/5 cup vinegar</li>\n<li>1/2 cup olive oil</li>\n<li>1 tsp salt</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 id=\"1-place-all-ingredients-in-a-blender--pulse-until-all-ingredients-reach-desired-texture\"><a href=\"#1-place-all-ingredients-in-a-blender--pulse-until-all-ingredients-reach-desired-texture\" aria-label=\"1 place all ingredients in a blender  pulse until all ingredients reach desired texture permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>1. Place all ingredients in a blender.  Pulse until all ingredients reach desired texture.</h4>\n<figure> <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 726px;\">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/63d10d69284548e75ae7100ccbd458e6/4e1b0/83-7.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"83 7\" title=\"83 7\" src=\"/static/63d10d69284548e75ae7100ccbd458e6/4e1b0/83-7.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/63d10d69284548e75ae7100ccbd458e6/90185/83-7.jpg 450w,\n/static/63d10d69284548e75ae7100ccbd458e6/4e1b0/83-7.jpg 726w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 726px) 100vw, 726px\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span> </figure>\n<p>To Assemble:</p>\n<h4 id=\"1-place-arepa-on-bottom-of-the-plate